  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zambia Drought response EA 01/2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following the drought which was a result of the prolonged dry spells for the period December 2018 to March 2019 experienced in Southern and Western province of Zambia, Caritas Zambia decided to launch an Emergency Appeal. The goal of this emergency response is to provide emergency relief and recovery assistance to drought-affected households in targeted districts of Western and Southern provinces of Zambia. The intervention will contribute to achieving food and nutrition security and sustainable livelihoods of 9,000 households affected by the dry spells experienced during the 2018/19 agricultural production season.  

This goal will be attained through the following three priority response objectives:
- To reduce food consumption gaps of the affected population 
- Agricultural production in target areas is sustainable compared to 2019
- To promote good nutrition</narrative>
  </description>
